<section class="report-page"><div class="report-inner"><header class="report-header"><h1>03 | Proof map, objection and discovery</h1><img src="assets/brand/universal-orlando-logo.png" alt="Universal Orlando Resort"></header><section class="report-section"><h2>Proof map</h2><table class="phase-table"><tr><th>Role need</th><th>Verified adjacent evidence</th></tr><tr><td>Enterprise AI and automation leadership</td><td>AI-first operating transformation at Vape-Jet; AI-readiness and agentic workflow design through DudeWorth since 2017.</td></tr><tr><td>Scale and always-on operations</td><td>Amazon Prime Pittsburgh launch and 24/7 operating mechanisms supporting approximately five million second-day orders annually.</td></tr><tr><td>Technical delivery and quality</td><td>Engineering, manufacturing, quality, customer delivery and process control in high-reliability electronics at Compunetics.</td></tr><tr><td>Responsible autonomy</td><td>Regulated drone operations with a 100% safety record and TensorFlow-based computer-vision concepts at ZeusVu.</td></tr><tr><td>Cross-functional change</td><td>Repeated work connecting operators, engineers, quality, customers, vendors, systems and executives.</td></tr></table><h2>The strongest objection</h2><p>Russell does not claim a PhD, a career as an ML research scientist, or years of ownership of a named enterprise MLOps platform. The role may prefer a leader with deeper recent production ML engineering credentials.</p><p><strong>Response:</strong> own the gap. Test whether the organization needs only the deepest individual model builder, or a technical director who can recruit and challenge specialists, connect architecture to live operations, establish production and governance mechanisms, and make AI adopted and measurable.</p><h2>Questions to test the thesis</h2><ol><li>What currently separates an approved experiment from a production service?</li><li>Where are decision rights unclear across product, data science, engineering, cyber, privacy and operations?</li><li>Which AI use cases carry the greatest guest-experience or continuity consequence?</li><li>What technical depth exists on the team today, and what must this director recruit?</li><li>What evidence would make year one unmistakably successful?</li></ol></section><footer class="page-footer"><span>Russell Dudek | Interview thesis brief</span><span>4</span></footer></div></section>
<section class="report-page"><div class="report-inner"><header class="report-header"><h1>04 | Sources and boundaries</h1><img src="assets/brand/universal-orlando-logo.png" alt="Universal Orlando Resort"></header><section class="report-section"><h2>Evidence boundaries</h2><div class="report-grid-3"><div class="report-card"><h3>Documented</h3><p>The job description, public company signals, official identity and verified candidate evidence.</p></div><div class="report-card"><h3>Inferred</h3><p>The actual mandate, operating tensions and proposed decision architecture - clearly framed for discovery.</p></div><div class="report-card"><h3>Unknown</h3><p>Universal's internal portfolio, architecture, data estate, vendors, budgets, staffing, controls and incidents.</p></div></div><ul><li>No claim is made about Universal's undisclosed AI portfolio, architecture, data estate, model vendors, team structure, budgets or internal incidents.</li><li>Company-specific recommendations are hypotheses for discovery, not assertions about current operations.</li><li>Candidate claims are limited to verified career evidence. Concepts are not presented as production deployments.</li></ul><h2>Public sources</h2><ol class="source-list"><li>Universal Orlando Resort, official destination site: four-park portfolio, Epic Universe and seamless trip-planning features. https://www.universalorlando.com/web/en/us</li><li>Universal Destinations &amp; Experiences, official corporate communications: portfolio description and current expansion signals. https://corporate.universaldestinationsandexperiences.com/</li><li>Universal Orlando Resort job posting, Director, Artificial Intelligence Technology. https://careers.pageuppeople.com/851/cw/en-us/job/665087/director-artificial-intelligence-technology</li><li>Reuters, May 22, 2025: Epic Universe investment, footprint and growth strategy.</li><li>Associated Press, 2025: Epic Universe described by Universal officials as its most technologically advanced park.</li></ol><h2>Candidate materials</h2><p>Candidate vision: https://russelldudek.github.io/</p><p>Public campaign repository: https://github.com/russelldudek/universal</p><p>LinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/in/russelldudek</p><div class="callout">Evaluation request: test the judgment behind the thesis, the transferability of the evidence, the ability to recruit specialist depth, and the discipline to state gaps without manufacturing certainty.</div></section><footer class="page-footer"><span>Russell Dudek | Interview thesis brief</span><span>5</span></footer></div></section></main></body></html>